        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): fetch quoted content before empty-message guard",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix #90177 — Feishu group reply with only `@bot` gets dropped before quoted content is fetched.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Feishu group reply with only `@bot` mention (no additional text) is no longer dropped before quoted content is fetched. The empty-message guard now runs after fetching the quoted parent message.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Ubuntu 22.04, OpenClaw `main` (ce0d5117bf), Node 22.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n1. `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/feishu/src/bot.test.ts` — targeted regression test passes\n2. `pnpm test extensions/feishu` — all 855 Feishu tests pass (new test included)\n3. `pnpm build:ci-artifacts` — build succeeds\n4. `pnpm ui:build` — UI build succeeds\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n\nNew regression test `\"does not drop empty-text message when it quotes a parent message (#90177)\"` added at `extensions/feishu/src/bot.test.ts:3747`. The test creates a Feishu message with empty text content and `parent_id` set, mocks `getMessageFeishu` to return valid quoted content, and verifies the handler dispatches a reply instead of dropping the event:\n\n```\n ✓ |extension-feishu| extensions/feishu/src/bot.test.ts > ... > does not drop empty-text message when it quotes a parent message (#90177) 5ms\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  74 passed (74)\n```\n\nFull Feishu test suite: 855/856 tests pass (1 pre-existing i18n string mismatch in `setup-surface.test.ts`, unrelated to this change).\n\n**Observed result after fix**:\n- Before: `skipping empty message (no text, no media) from ou_xxx` — event dropped before quoted fetch\n- After: Quoted content is fetched first; empty-message guard only skips when current text, media list, AND quoted content are all empty\n- The new test proves the combined (empty text + quoted content) path works end-to-end\n\n**What was not tested**: Live Feishu E2E with real bot credentials. The fix is a logic reorder that exactly matches the root cause and minimal fix direction described in the issue. The regression test covers the exact scenario (empty text + parentId + mock quoted content → dispatch expected).\n\n## Out-of-scope follow-ups\n\nLive Feishu E2E test (requires Feishu bot credentials). The deterministic regression test verifies the logic path at the unit level.\n\nFixes #90177",
        "branch": "fix/90177-feishu-empty-reply-with-quote",
